    <item>
      <title>Re: Translation not working in v1.1</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezcomments/forum/general/translation_not_working_in_v1_1/re_translation_not_working_in_v1_1</link>
      <description>Hello Javier,&#13;
&#13;
Sorry maybe it's a little confusing, but the Language is used for something else:	&#13;
&#13;
it is the language of reCAPTCHA when the theme is not 'custom'. &#13;
&#13;
from http://doc.ez.no/Extensions/eZ-Comments/Setup-and-user-guide-1.1/ezcomments.ini-settings&#13;
&#13;
&#13;
By default(theme is custom), the language mechanism of recaptcha is the same as ez publish translation, meaning that if you want to use one language, you need to have translation file(translation.ts) in that language and siteaccess is using that language..&#13;
&#13;
--&#13;
Best regards&#13;
Chen</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Chen Xiongjie)</author>
